WEBVTT

00:01.068 --> 00:03.471
* Until I get the nerve

00:03.504 --> 00:08.375
* To sound what we believe

00:08.409 --> 00:12.580
* When I see your face

00:12.612 --> 00:16.250
* My eyes just dilate

00:16.283 --> 00:19.253
(indistinct chatter)
* But I can't erase

00:20.553 --> 00:24.358
* That I want to violate...

00:24.391 --> 00:26.359
Hey, look,
Parker's here.

00:26.393 --> 00:27.695
Yeah?

00:27.728 --> 00:29.196
You're not looking?

00:29.230 --> 00:31.364
He looks really cute
in green.

00:31.399 --> 00:32.700
Teal.

00:32.732 --> 00:35.368
He's reflected
in the mirror.

00:37.537 --> 00:41.008
You know, when you spend
all week with a boy,

00:41.040 --> 00:43.042
you are allowed to
look at him directly.

00:43.076 --> 00:45.012
Not all week.

00:45.045 --> 00:48.348
We hung out
moderately incessantly,

00:48.381 --> 00:50.218
but we're not here
together tonight.

00:50.250 --> 00:52.018
You know, I don't
want to crowd him.

00:52.051 --> 00:54.255
(applause and cheering)

01:00.761 --> 01:03.097
Hey. You guys ready
to load up and go?

01:03.131 --> 01:04.730
Almost.

01:04.765 --> 01:06.534
Buffy's looking at Parker,

01:06.567 --> 01:10.204
who, it turns out, has a
reflection, so, big plus there.

01:10.237 --> 01:13.406
Buffy's having lusty
wrong feelings.

01:13.441 --> 01:14.942
No, I'm not.

01:14.974 --> 01:17.043
No, you're not.

01:17.076 --> 01:18.778
Oh, I so am.

01:18.811 --> 01:22.783
No, they're not wrong feelings,
'cause there's no wrong.

01:22.816 --> 01:25.385
You're free, you're
both grown-ups.

01:25.418 --> 01:27.855
You are free, right?

01:29.088 --> 01:30.724
Hi.
Hi.

01:30.757 --> 01:33.561
I... I just wanted to let you
know I'm heading out.

01:33.593 --> 01:35.795
And it's not real safe
around here, so, if you,

01:35.829 --> 01:37.397
you know, walk back
to your dorm...

01:37.430 --> 01:40.768
How silly of me not
to plan ahead.

01:46.939 --> 01:48.475
Bye.
PARKER:
See you guys.

01:48.509 --> 01:51.078
* Every time you're near

01:51.110 --> 01:54.281
* I'll keep you safe
from harm... *

01:54.314 --> 01:55.748
(distant siren blaring)

01:55.783 --> 01:57.651
That was, like,
the best set ever.

01:57.685 --> 01:59.186
We'll do great in L.A.

01:59.219 --> 02:01.087
We're gonna have them
glued to their seats.

02:01.120 --> 02:02.355
Uh, Devon?

02:02.390 --> 02:04.090
Aren't they
supposed to dance?

02:04.123 --> 02:06.527
Well, we can glue 'em
to the dance floor.

02:09.628 --> 02:11.598
I don't mean
with real glue.

02:11.632 --> 02:13.000
You got that, right?

02:13.032 --> 02:15.203
I got that.

02:15.235 --> 02:17.538
HARMONY:
Willow?

02:17.570 --> 02:20.274
WILLOW:
Harmony, hey.

02:20.307 --> 02:21.942
Hey, I haven't seen you since...

02:21.974 --> 02:23.644
Since graduation.

02:23.676 --> 02:25.646
Big snake, huh?
Yeah.

02:25.679 --> 02:28.382
So how was your summer vacation?

02:28.415 --> 02:31.185
Oh, well, I was gonna go
to France, but I didn't.

02:31.218 --> 02:33.152
I was dying to
see the stores.

02:33.187 --> 02:35.323
Oh, and museums.

02:35.355 --> 02:37.156
Museums?

02:37.191 --> 02:39.126
Yeah, I heard they had 'em.

02:39.158 --> 02:41.295
You know, just a rumor
you pick up on the streets.
(laughing)

02:41.329 --> 02:43.129
Right. You're always so funny,
Willow.

02:43.163 --> 02:44.632
You haven't changed a bit.

02:44.664 --> 02:46.667
No, you, neither.

02:46.699 --> 02:49.102
Oh... maybe a little.

02:51.204 --> 02:52.872
(gasps)
(growls)

02:52.906 --> 02:54.942
(yelps)

02:56.877 --> 03:00.013
(wolf howling)

03:00.046 --> 03:02.250
*

03:50.298 --> 03:54.301
(growling, grunting)

03:54.335 --> 03:55.902
Back off, Harmony!
(growling)

03:55.936 --> 03:58.639
Okay, fine.

03:58.671 --> 04:01.308
Hide behind your boyfriend,
but guess what?

04:01.342 --> 04:04.312
I have a boyfriend, too,
and he's gonna be mad that

04:04.344 --> 04:06.013
you were mean to me.

04:10.783 --> 04:12.453
BUFFY:
Hobbies?

04:12.485 --> 04:15.087
Yeah, hobbies, interests.

04:15.122 --> 04:17.658
I feel like there's so much
I still don't know about you.

04:17.690 --> 04:20.327
What do you like to do?

04:20.360 --> 04:27.468
Well, mostly I... hang
out and... do stuff.

04:27.500 --> 04:31.672
Yeah, I was into that
for a while.

04:31.704 --> 04:33.574
What's that?

04:33.606 --> 04:35.242
What's what?

04:35.274 --> 04:37.076
You have a scar.

04:37.110 --> 04:40.848
Right. Um...

04:40.880 --> 04:43.016
Angry puppy.

04:44.851 --> 04:48.689
So, do I get to see
any of your scars?

04:48.721 --> 04:50.858
(laughs) Oh.

04:50.891 --> 04:53.761
Oh, mine are all psychological.

04:53.793 --> 04:55.896
Oh, please. Those
are the best kind.

04:57.665 --> 05:00.800
Well, my father
died last year.

05:00.834 --> 05:03.704
Oh, God. Parker,
I'm sorry.

05:03.737 --> 05:05.706
I didn't mean to
bring up that stuff.

05:05.738 --> 05:07.708
Oh, bad, bad Buffy.

05:07.740 --> 05:10.711
No. No, I'm okay
to talk about it now.

05:10.744 --> 05:13.547
And I'm not doing the deep,
get-sympathy routine.

05:13.581 --> 05:16.384
I mean, don't you just
hate guys who are all

05:16.417 --> 05:20.353
"I'm dark and brooding,
so give me love."?

05:20.387 --> 05:22.755
I don't think I've
ever met that type.

05:31.031 --> 05:33.533
I just wanted to say that

05:33.567 --> 05:38.538
what made it so sad was that
there was, oh, a lot of stuff

05:38.572 --> 05:40.139
he didn't get to finish.

05:40.173 --> 05:42.475
It made me think about...

05:42.509 --> 05:44.211
(laughs)

05:44.244 --> 05:47.781
you know... living for now.

05:51.619 --> 05:54.187
I think about that sometimes.

05:54.221 --> 05:57.557
Yeah, I sort of...

05:57.591 --> 05:59.992
drowned a couple years ago,

06:00.026 --> 06:03.596
but I came back, obviously.

06:05.533 --> 06:07.767
But I don't... I don't
put stuff off anymore,

06:07.800 --> 06:09.769
like you were saying.

06:09.802 --> 06:11.771
That's great.

06:11.805 --> 06:15.375
I mean, everybody
says they get it.

06:15.408 --> 06:17.343
"Oh, man, me, too.
Live for today."

06:17.377 --> 06:19.612
But what they really want
is an excuse to goof off

06:19.646 --> 06:21.014
and not study for finals.

06:21.048 --> 06:23.016
Also a valid life choice.

06:23.050 --> 06:24.584
(laughs)

06:26.052 --> 06:28.422
It's cool to
find someone else

06:28.456 --> 06:30.757
who understands.

06:32.826 --> 06:35.896
So, Parker Abrams,
when you go to sleep tonight,

06:35.928 --> 06:38.499
what are you gonna regret
not doing today?

06:39.932 --> 06:44.036
I am going to regret
being too nervous

06:44.071 --> 06:48.341
to ask you to go to the party
at Wolf House tomorrow night.

06:50.110 --> 06:52.646
Do you want to go
to the party...?
Yes.

06:58.586 --> 07:00.788
XANDER:
 I'm not enjoying this.

07:00.821 --> 07:02.790
Well, shelve them correctly,
and we can finish.

07:02.822 --> 07:04.824
I don't get your
crazy system.

07:04.858 --> 07:07.194
My system? It's
called the alphabet.

07:08.596 --> 07:11.564
Huh. Would you look at that.

07:11.598 --> 07:14.166
(door opens)

07:16.435 --> 07:19.005
You should lock your door.

07:19.038 --> 07:21.475
Believe me, I am kicking myself.

07:21.509 --> 07:23.110
XANDER:
Anya?

07:23.143 --> 07:26.779
Last time I saw you,
fleeing in terror.

07:26.814 --> 07:28.949
How'd that work out for you?

07:28.981 --> 07:30.651
I need to talk to Xander.

07:33.452 --> 07:35.855
Go away.

07:39.627 --> 07:41.562
Xander, come with me.

07:45.197 --> 07:46.800
Your mother said you
were working here?

07:46.834 --> 07:48.636
Yeah. Yeah,
need some money, and...

07:48.668 --> 07:51.170
So, where is our
relationship going?

07:51.204 --> 07:54.307
Our what? Our who?

07:54.341 --> 07:56.442
Relationship. What
kind do we have,

07:56.475 --> 07:58.045
and what is it
progressing toward?

07:58.077 --> 08:00.447
I...

08:00.480 --> 08:02.783
Uh, we have a relationship?

08:02.815 --> 08:04.617
We went to the prom.

08:04.651 --> 08:08.689
Yeah. On our one and only date.

08:08.721 --> 08:12.024
Second date called on account
of snake, remember?

08:12.059 --> 08:14.827
And there's the whole you used
to be a man-killing demon thing,

08:14.862 --> 08:19.365
which to be fair, is as much
my issue as it is yours.

08:19.399 --> 08:22.168
I can't stop thinking about you.

08:22.201 --> 08:25.572
Sometimes, in my dreams,
you're all naked.

08:25.605 --> 08:27.206
Really? (laughs)

08:27.240 --> 08:29.543
You know, if I'm in the checkout
line at the Wal-Mart,

08:29.576 --> 08:32.345
I've had that same one.
So,

08:32.379 --> 08:34.748
I can assume a standing
Friday night date

08:34.782 --> 08:36.750
and a mutual recognition
of prom night

08:36.783 --> 08:39.586
as our dating
anniversary?
Anya, slow down.

08:39.620 --> 08:41.721
In fact, come
to a screeching halt.

08:41.754 --> 08:45.692
See, these things kind of have
to develop on their own.

08:45.725 --> 08:47.595
All right. How?

08:47.628 --> 08:52.532
I don't know.
It just... happens.

08:56.870 --> 09:01.008
This is it.
My door. Wood.

09:01.041 --> 09:03.677
Maybe some kind
of wood veneer.

09:03.711 --> 09:05.712
It's nice.

09:10.717 --> 09:12.085
OZ:
Hey.

09:12.119 --> 09:14.955
Hi. Hi. Uh,
remember Harmony?

09:14.988 --> 09:16.789
She's back
from her summer vacation,

09:16.823 --> 09:18.859
and she's a little different.

09:18.892 --> 09:20.293
Different?

09:20.326 --> 09:23.263
Paler?
Is your neck okay?

09:23.296 --> 09:25.398
Neck. Paler.

09:25.432 --> 09:27.100
Puppy. The angry puppy.

09:27.134 --> 09:30.570
Yeah, we came to warn you
about the... angry puppy.

09:30.604 --> 09:32.806
Uh, uh, I'm...

09:32.840 --> 09:34.774
should really take care
of this now.
Oh.

09:34.807 --> 09:36.543
I'll pick you up tomorrow
night for the party?

09:36.576 --> 09:38.110
I can't wait.

09:40.614 --> 09:43.015
Band-Aid, now.

09:44.751 --> 09:46.886
Thank you.

09:46.919 --> 09:50.222
BUFFY:
Harmony's a vampire?

09:50.256 --> 09:52.325
She must be dying
without a reflection.

09:52.359 --> 09:54.662
She just made me so mad.

09:54.695 --> 09:56.996
"My boyfriend's
gonna beat you up."

09:57.029 --> 09:58.264
My boyfriend?

09:58.298 --> 09:59.832
Well, I mean,
if you believe her.

09:59.866 --> 10:01.735
She always lied
about stuff like that.

10:01.769 --> 10:03.403
"Oh, he goes
to another school.

10:03.436 --> 10:05.172
You wouldn't know him."

10:05.205 --> 10:08.140
Uh, Devon dated her for a while,
but she was too flaky for him

10:08.174 --> 10:11.177
which, stop and marvel
at the concept.
(laughs)

10:11.211 --> 10:13.647
Guy dating Harmony dead.

10:13.681 --> 10:16.750
Must be, like, the most tolerant
guy in the world.

10:16.783 --> 10:19.186
(drilling)

10:25.357 --> 10:28.061
Hi, baby. I'm back.

10:38.071 --> 10:40.506
(indistinct chatter,
dog barking)

10:47.080 --> 10:48.948
(drilling)

10:48.981 --> 10:50.884
It's definitely
the crypt, Ryan?

10:50.918 --> 10:53.019
I'm not keen on tunneling
into someone's septic tank.

10:53.052 --> 10:54.822
It's the crypt.

10:54.855 --> 10:56.655
The radar soundings are clear.

10:56.690 --> 10:59.826
Uh, the walls are thinnest
here at the bottom.

10:59.860 --> 11:01.794
We have to tunnel
from underneath.

11:01.828 --> 11:05.032
More work, but, uh,
I'm sure that you...

11:05.065 --> 11:06.298
(grunts, whimpering)

11:06.332 --> 11:09.201
You'd better be
more than sure, mate,

11:09.235 --> 11:11.739
'cause I'd hate
to have to hurt you.
I

11:11.772 --> 11:13.539
swear. I swear.

11:13.572 --> 11:17.076
How's my little
Blondie Bear?

11:17.110 --> 11:20.047
Harm, does this look
like a good time to talk?

11:20.080 --> 11:22.315
Are you gonna
kill Willow today?

11:22.349 --> 11:23.884
'Cause I want you to say,

11:23.917 --> 11:25.753
"This is for messing
with my sweet girl."

11:25.786 --> 11:27.754
And then... you know...

11:27.788 --> 11:30.423
(sucking)

11:30.456 --> 11:32.860
(gasps, panting)

11:34.061 --> 11:36.062
Nobody knows I'm here.

11:36.096 --> 11:37.931
Now, I'm not killing
the slayer's best friend,

11:37.965 --> 11:39.599
as that would
tend to announce

11:39.631 --> 11:41.902
my presence, and
we're too bloody close.

11:41.934 --> 11:44.437
You almost killed her last year.
Suddenly it's a big deal?

11:44.471 --> 11:46.673
Sod off! Hmm?

11:46.706 --> 11:48.741
Go eat something.
I've got work to do.

11:52.144 --> 11:53.780
(sighs)

11:55.715 --> 11:58.051
(soft groaning)
This one tastes funny.

11:58.085 --> 11:59.451
Take me out to eat.

11:59.485 --> 12:00.921
He's perfectly fresh.

12:00.953 --> 12:02.755
(soft groaning)

12:02.789 --> 12:05.692
I think I had a math class
with him last year, and I didn't

12:05.725 --> 12:07.726
like him that
much then, either.
Harm!

12:07.760 --> 12:09.296
I want to go to a party!

12:09.328 --> 12:11.230
(stomps his foot)

12:11.264 --> 12:13.732
(grunts loudly)

12:13.767 --> 12:17.136
Ooh. Right here, baby?

12:17.169 --> 12:18.971
In front of Ryan?

12:19.005 --> 12:21.607
You'd like that, wouldn't you?

12:21.640 --> 12:24.744
Maybe I would.

12:24.778 --> 12:26.479
After a party.

12:26.513 --> 12:29.817
(laughing)

12:32.085 --> 12:33.886
Tonight...

12:33.921 --> 12:35.956
I'll take you somewhere nice.

12:40.027 --> 12:43.163
* I stand in the pouring rain

12:43.196 --> 12:46.066
* You couldn't even be there
to pick me up *

12:46.099 --> 12:48.434
* Taking me
for granted again *

12:48.467 --> 12:51.138
* You're running out of time
and you're out of luck *

12:51.171 --> 12:55.174
* Just a moment of weakness...

12:55.207 --> 12:57.977
This is some party, huh?
The last days of Rome.

12:58.010 --> 13:01.148
It's better.
No old Romans.
(laughs)

13:01.181 --> 13:02.950
(glass breaking, men groaning)

13:02.982 --> 13:04.451
You want to dance?

13:04.484 --> 13:07.720
No! Let's have
a meaningful talk instead.

13:09.822 --> 13:13.025
Spike.

13:13.059 --> 13:15.595
And Harmony.

13:15.628 --> 13:17.697
Buffy. Hi.

13:17.730 --> 13:20.200
What a cute outfit... last year.

13:20.232 --> 13:23.036
SPIKE:
Well, this
is interesting.

13:23.070 --> 13:26.940
It's, uh, sort of a double date.

13:26.974 --> 13:29.509
Looks like your friend started
the party a little early,

13:29.542 --> 13:31.311
huh?
(Spike laughs)

13:31.344 --> 13:34.847
Say, let's have a look
at the new boy.

13:34.881 --> 13:37.350
Hi. I'm Parker.

13:39.251 --> 13:41.889
SPIKE:
I like him.

13:41.922 --> 13:44.823
He's got, um... What's the word?

13:44.857 --> 13:47.226
Vulnerability.

13:47.259 --> 13:49.328
And you're with Harmony. Hmm.
What, did you lose a bet?

13:49.361 --> 13:51.298
Hey!
Actually,

13:51.331 --> 13:53.033
uh, how we met? It's, um...

13:53.066 --> 13:54.902
It's a funny story,
really. It's...

13:54.934 --> 13:56.336
(groaning)

13:56.369 --> 13:58.504
Stay here!

14:00.840 --> 14:04.677
(tires squealing,
engine revving and retreating)

14:04.711 --> 14:07.179
(indistinct crowd chatter)

14:18.958 --> 14:21.561
(twig snaps)

14:21.594 --> 14:23.263
(grunting)

14:23.296 --> 14:26.832
What's the matter, Spike?
Dru dump you again?

14:26.865 --> 14:29.036
(grunting)

14:29.068 --> 14:30.870
Maybe I dumped her!

14:30.903 --> 14:32.338
(grunting)

14:32.371 --> 14:35.241
She left him for a fungus demon.
That's all

14:35.274 --> 14:38.278
he talks about
most days.
Harm!

14:38.311 --> 14:40.080
We are going.

14:40.113 --> 14:42.548
It isn't time yet.

14:42.581 --> 14:45.085
Yeah, but as soon
as we have the Gem of Amara,

14:45.118 --> 14:46.719
you're gonna be sorry...
(loud grunting)

14:46.753 --> 14:49.121
Sor... What? Ow!

14:54.760 --> 14:57.129
(rhythmic chugging
of washing machine)

15:02.568 --> 15:04.636
(knocking)

15:04.671 --> 15:06.306
Come in.

15:12.078 --> 15:15.315
Anya. Hi again.

15:15.347 --> 15:17.951
Your mother sent me around
from the front of the house.

15:17.985 --> 15:19.918
She also said
to ask you to add

15:19.952 --> 15:21.821
fabric softener
when the timer goes off.

15:21.854 --> 15:25.758
Can we talk some more?
Yeah. I suppose.

15:25.792 --> 15:27.159
Would you care
for something?

15:27.193 --> 15:29.928
I have cran-apple.
All right.

15:31.931 --> 15:35.434
You know, it is customary
to call before

15:35.467 --> 15:39.438
you show up, not that...

15:39.471 --> 15:42.642
BUFFY:
 Yeah.

15:42.674 --> 15:45.345
Spike with Harmony,
if you can believe it.

15:45.378 --> 15:47.313
I couldn't figure out
why he ran away,

15:47.346 --> 15:49.481
but Harmony said something,

15:49.515 --> 15:50.917
why they were here.

15:50.950 --> 15:52.585
They were looking
for the Gem of something.

15:52.619 --> 15:54.520
Um... Amara.

15:54.553 --> 15:56.155
The Gem of Amara.
Are you sure?

15:56.188 --> 15:58.091
Yeah. What's up?

15:58.125 --> 16:01.028
Uh, it's just it's, um...
it's not real.

16:01.061 --> 16:03.163
It's like the, uh,
the vampire equivalent

16:03.196 --> 16:05.365
of the, uh... the holy grail,

16:05.398 --> 16:08.268
a source of some...
enormous power

16:08.301 --> 16:10.836
which is conveniently vague.

16:10.870 --> 16:15.508
Uh... I think.
Here it is. Yes. Um,

16:15.542 --> 16:17.344
"There was a great deal
of vampiric interest

16:17.376 --> 16:19.011
in locating the gem during..."

16:19.046 --> 16:21.780
Oh, the tenth century.

16:21.813 --> 16:24.551
"Questing vampires
combed the Earth,

16:24.583 --> 16:26.119
"but no one found it.

16:26.153 --> 16:28.020
It was concluded
that it never existed."

16:28.054 --> 16:29.956
Well, Spike seems
to think it exists,

16:29.989 --> 16:31.957
and he's looking in Sunnydale.

16:31.990 --> 16:35.227
Yes. Well, I'll research it
as best I can.

16:35.261 --> 16:37.629
You've done all you can
for tonight. Go to bed.

16:37.663 --> 16:38.865
Uh-huh.

16:38.898 --> 16:40.866
Sleepy. Yawn.

16:40.899 --> 16:42.168
Bye.

16:47.374 --> 16:49.176
Is Antonio Banderas
a vampire?

16:49.209 --> 16:51.344
No.

16:51.378 --> 16:52.678
Oh.

16:52.711 --> 16:55.548
Can I make him a vampire?

16:55.581 --> 16:56.849
No.

16:59.086 --> 17:00.687
Wait. On second
thought, yeah.

17:00.720 --> 17:02.754
Go do that.

17:02.788 --> 17:04.021
Take your time.

17:04.057 --> 17:06.558
