34:48.652 --> 34:50.255
She's a friend of yours?

34:50.289 --> 34:52.757
Yeah, you'd like her a bunch.

34:52.791 --> 34:55.059
So, what's up?

34:55.092 --> 34:59.097
Well, um, you didn't call.

34:59.130 --> 35:01.666
I... I mean,
I'd understand, you know,

35:01.699 --> 35:04.603
if you were busy
or sick or something.

35:04.635 --> 35:06.070
It's only been a
couple of days.

35:06.103 --> 35:08.639
You need to talk to
me about something?

35:08.673 --> 35:11.277
Is everything okay?

35:11.309 --> 35:13.244
Sure it is.

35:13.278 --> 35:15.981
It is?
Sure.

35:16.014 --> 35:20.286
Oh, um, so, maybe do you want
to... do something?

35:20.318 --> 35:22.820
We could do that. Absolutely.

35:22.853 --> 35:25.356
Great. How about tonight?

35:25.391 --> 35:27.925
Oh. Well, the thing is,

35:27.958 --> 35:32.130
I think I'm supposed to get
together with some people later.

35:33.731 --> 35:36.967
Parker, um, did I...?

35:40.539 --> 35:43.208
Did I do something wrong?

35:43.242 --> 35:44.842
Something wrong?

35:44.876 --> 35:47.045
No, of course not.

35:47.077 --> 35:48.880
It was fun.

35:48.914 --> 35:50.715
Didn't you have fun?

35:50.748 --> 35:53.952
I mean, watch out
how you answer that.

35:53.985 --> 35:55.387
My ego is fragile.

35:55.420 --> 35:57.789
You had fun?

35:57.822 --> 35:59.858
Is that all it was?

35:59.891 --> 36:02.027
Well, what else was
it supposed to be?

36:04.929 --> 36:07.666
It seemed... like...

36:07.699 --> 36:09.867
you liked me.

36:09.900 --> 36:11.802
I do.

36:11.836 --> 36:15.206
But I'm starting to feel like
you thought that meant... what?

36:15.240 --> 36:18.009
Some kind of commitment?

36:18.043 --> 36:21.112
I mean, is that really
what you want right now?

36:22.380 --> 36:26.016
I just... thought...

36:26.050 --> 36:30.188
Look, I'm sorry if you
misunderstood something. I...

36:30.222 --> 36:33.057
I... I thought
things were pretty clear.

36:33.090 --> 36:36.027
I-I didn't mean to mis...

36:36.061 --> 36:39.030
I'm-I'm s... I'm sorry.

36:40.231 --> 36:43.268
Look, I really have to go now.

36:51.041 --> 36:53.711
Parker, wait!

36:53.744 --> 36:55.547
I did this all wrong.

36:55.581 --> 36:58.617
No, it's cool.
We'll hook up later.

36:58.650 --> 37:02.420
SPIKE:
Well, that was pathetic.

37:07.793 --> 37:09.795
SPIKE:
What a fantastic day.

37:09.827 --> 37:12.697
Birds singin', squirrels makin'
lots of rotten little squirrels,

37:12.731 --> 37:15.967
sun beamin' down
in a nice non-fatal way.

37:16.001 --> 37:17.302
It's very exciting.

37:17.335 --> 37:18.704
Can't wait to see if I freckle.

37:18.737 --> 37:22.907
(grunting)

37:29.114 --> 37:33.485
Oh, do it again. It tickles.
(squishy whooshing)

37:33.518 --> 37:34.985
You know, in a good way.

37:35.019 --> 37:37.222
The gem.
Oh, yeah.

37:37.255 --> 37:40.025
The Gem of Amara.

37:42.027 --> 37:45.563
Official sponsor
of my killing you.

37:45.597 --> 37:47.298
(growling)

37:51.670 --> 37:54.306
WILLOW:
Harmony?

37:56.375 --> 37:59.177
(crying):
Being a vampire sucks.

37:59.210 --> 38:00.679
(sighs)

38:00.711 --> 38:02.112
(growling)

38:02.146 --> 38:04.516
Buffy!

38:07.152 --> 38:09.820
Xander. I...
I was looking for you.

38:09.855 --> 38:11.657
You weren't
in your musty basement.

38:11.690 --> 38:14.125
Have you seen Buffy?
No.

38:14.159 --> 38:17.362
Uh, about, you know,
what happened, um...

38:17.396 --> 38:19.498
When I said I was over you--
I mean, I really...

38:19.530 --> 38:22.233
Anya, I don't have time.

38:25.170 --> 38:27.505
GILES:
 Harmony,

38:27.539 --> 38:30.208
where's Spike?

38:30.240 --> 38:32.143
Does he have the gem?

38:35.179 --> 38:37.382
He staked me,
and then he took it.

38:37.416 --> 38:39.851
He tried to take it
right off my finger.

38:39.885 --> 38:42.954
Like I wouldn't have
just given it to him.

38:42.987 --> 38:44.789
I would have given him
anything he wanted.

38:44.822 --> 38:47.693
He was my platinum baby,
and I loved him.

38:47.726 --> 38:49.927
Where did Spike go?

38:53.998 --> 38:57.568
(grunting)

39:04.342 --> 39:06.878
Aah!
(growling)

39:06.911 --> 39:10.416
(grunting, bones crunching)

39:13.117 --> 39:15.586
(grunts, growling)

39:15.621 --> 39:20.025
(grunting)

39:28.032 --> 39:31.436
Getting tired, Slayer?

39:33.137 --> 39:36.407
(growling)
(both grunting)

39:39.143 --> 39:42.146
(grunting)
BUFFY:
Xander? Get out of here!

39:46.083 --> 39:50.021
So, you let Parker
take a poke, eh?

39:50.054 --> 39:52.557
Didn't seem like
you knew each other that well.

39:52.590 --> 39:54.693
What exactly did it take
to pry apart

39:54.726 --> 39:56.561
the slayer's dimpled knees?

39:56.594 --> 39:58.195
You're a pig, Spike.

39:58.228 --> 40:00.731
(growls, both grunting)

40:00.766 --> 40:03.400
Did he play the sensitive lad
and get you to seduce him?

40:03.434 --> 40:06.403
That's a good trick if the
girl's thick enough to buy it.

40:06.438 --> 40:08.940
(grunting)

40:08.974 --> 40:11.909
I wonder what you did wrong.

40:11.943 --> 40:13.978
Uh, too strong?

40:14.012 --> 40:16.114
Did you bruise the boy?

40:16.146 --> 40:20.284
Whatever. Guess you're
not worth a second go.

40:20.318 --> 40:22.621
Come to think of it, seems like
someone told me as much.

40:22.653 --> 40:25.322
Who was that? Oh, yeah.

40:25.356 --> 40:27.125
Angel.

40:31.996 --> 40:35.132
(grunting)

40:38.268 --> 40:41.405
Ugh! Take it off me this way,

40:41.438 --> 40:43.340
we both burn!
Really?

40:43.373 --> 40:45.577
Let's see.

40:45.610 --> 40:47.445
(Spike growling,
hissing sound)

40:47.478 --> 40:50.014
Ow! Aah!

40:50.047 --> 40:52.182
(panting)

40:57.355 --> 40:59.123
WILLOW:
I like it.

40:59.157 --> 41:01.326
It's small.

41:01.358 --> 41:03.460
Really worth
getting my ribs bashed in.

41:03.494 --> 41:05.931
It's obviously very dangerous,
and, uh, we're destroying it.

41:05.963 --> 41:09.434
We don't
destroy it.

41:09.467 --> 41:11.436
Well, Buffy, any vampire
that gets his hands on this

41:11.469 --> 41:12.871
is going to be
essentially un-killable.

41:14.972 --> 41:17.242
Oh.

41:19.811 --> 41:21.612
OZ:
I have

41:21.646 --> 41:23.380
that gig in L.A.
I could swing by.

41:23.414 --> 41:25.282
Thanks, Oz.
XANDER:
What's going on?

41:25.315 --> 41:27.452
What's in L.A.?

41:27.485 --> 41:30.454
She's giving the ring to Angel.
Don't make a fuss.

41:30.487 --> 41:31.889
Buffy,

41:31.922 --> 41:34.291
are you sure?

41:34.324 --> 41:36.360
He should have it.

41:39.731 --> 41:42.467
BUFFY:
 So what I'm wondering is,

41:42.500 --> 41:45.335
does this always happen?

41:45.369 --> 41:49.807
Sleep with a guy,
and he goes all evil?

41:49.840 --> 41:51.976
God, I'm just a fool.

41:52.010 --> 41:54.344
Well, maybe you made a
mistake, but that's okay.

41:54.378 --> 41:57.849
Next time... What?

41:59.585 --> 42:03.188
Parker said it's okay
to make mistakes.

42:03.221 --> 42:06.190
It was sweet.

42:06.224 --> 42:07.826
No, it wasn't.

42:07.858 --> 42:09.827
He was saying that

42:09.860 --> 42:11.996
so you would take a
chance and sleep with him.

42:12.030 --> 42:14.532
He's a poophead.

42:15.733 --> 42:17.001
You're right.

42:17.034 --> 42:20.938
He's... manipulative
and shallow.

42:20.972 --> 42:23.074
And why doesn't he want me?

42:23.108 --> 42:24.943
Am I repulsive?

42:24.976 --> 42:28.679
If there was something repulsive
about me, you'd tell me, right?

42:28.713 --> 42:30.280
I'm your friend.

42:30.315 --> 42:33.284
I would call you
repulsive in a second.

42:34.719 --> 42:37.521
Maybe Parker and I
could still work it out.

42:37.554 --> 42:41.192
Do you... you think that
we could still work it out?

42:41.226 --> 42:42.860
I think you're missing something

42:42.893 --> 42:45.295
about the whole
poophead principle.

42:49.134 --> 42:51.202
You know, you go on ahead.

42:51.235 --> 42:54.438
I... I think
I'm gonna go take a walk.

42:54.472 --> 42:57.742
Are you sure?
Yeah.

43:20.130 --> 43:22.867
(sniffles)

44:08.045 --> 44:10.514
Grr. Argh.
